description: Returns a change set between the LIVE core network policy and a submitted policy.

parameters.name: CoreNetworkId
parameters.description: The ID of a core network.

parameters.name: PolicyVersionId
parameters.description: The ID of the policy version.

nested_items.name: CoreNetworkChanges
nested_items.description: Describes a core network changes.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: The type of change.

nested_items.name: Action
nested_items.description: The action to take for a core network.

nested_items.name: Identifier
nested_items.description: The resource identifier.

nested_items.name: PreviousValues
nested_items.description: The previous values for a core network.

nested_items.name: SegmentName
nested_items.description: The names of the segments in a core network.

nested_items.name: NetworkFunctionGroupName
nested_items.description: The network function group name if the change event is associated with a network function group.

nested_items.name: EdgeLocations
nested_items.description: The Regions where edges are located in a core network.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: Asn
nested_items.description: The ASN of a core network.

nested_items.name: Cidr
nested_items.description: The IP addresses used for a core network.

nested_items.name: DestinationIdentifier
nested_items.description: The ID of the destination.

nested_items.name: InsideCidrBlocks
nested_items.description: The inside IP addresses used for core network change values.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: SharedSegments
nested_items.description: The shared segments for a core network change value.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: ServiceInsertionActions
nested_items.description: Describes the service insertion action.

nested_items.name: Action
nested_items.description: The action the service insertion takes for traffic. send-via sends east-west traffic between attachments. send-to sends north-south traffic to the security appliance, and then from that to either the Internet or to an on-premesis location.

nested_items.name: Mode
nested_items.description: Describes the mode packets take for the send-via action. This is not used when the action is send-to. dual-hop packets traverse attachments in both the source to the destination core network edges. This mode requires that an inspection attachment must be present in all Regions of the service insertion-enabled segments. For single-hop, packets traverse a single intermediate inserted attachment. You can use EdgeOverride to specify a specific edge to use.

nested_items.name: WhenSentTo
nested_items.description: The list of destination segments if the service insertion action is send-via.

nested_items.name: WhenSentToSegmentsList
nested_items.description: The list of destination segments when the service insertion action is send-to.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: NetworkFunctionGroups
nested_items.description: The list of network function groups associated with the service insertion action.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the network function group.

nested_items.name: WithEdgeOverrides
nested_items.description: Describes any edge overrides. An edge override is a specific edge to be used for traffic.

nested_items.name: EdgeSets
nested_items.description: The list of edge locations.
(list) ---
(string) ---

nested_items.name: UseEdge
nested_items.description: The edge that should be used when overriding the current edge order.

nested_items.name: VpnEcmpSupport
nested_items.description: Indicates whether Equal Cost Multipath (ECMP) is enabled for the core network.

nested_items.name: DnsSupport
nested_items.description: Indicates whether public DNS support is supported. The default is true.

nested_items.name: SecurityGroupReferencingSupport
nested_items.description: Indicates whether security group referencing is enabled for the core network.

nested_items.name: NewValues
nested_items.description: The new value for a core network.
